98.7	Affordance	Affordance	An affordance is a quality of an object, or an environment, which allows an individual to perform an action. For example, a knob affords twisting, and perhaps pushing, while a cord affords pulling. The term is used in a variety of fields: perceptual psychology, cognitive psychology, environmental psychology, industrial design, humanâ€“computer interaction (HCI), interaction design, instructional design and artificial intelligence.	
